$ Oracle: V$TEMPORARY_LOBS
@ v$temporary_lobs

For → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/session[sessions] that are using → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/data-types/lob#ora-lob-3-types[temporary LOBs], `v$temporary_lobs` shows where the LOBs's data resides.

{ Columns

  table { ll
    `sid` ☰ The session identifier.
    `cache_lobs` ☰ Number of LOBs in the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/logical-structures/tablespace/temporary using *cache*.
    `nocache_lobs` ☰ Number of LOBs in the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/logical-structures/tablespace/temporary not using *cache*.
    `abstract_lobs` ☰ Number of LOBs in the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/PGA.
    `con_id` ☰ The pluggable database container id.

  table }

}

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views
